WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:02:15.850 --> 00:02:17.090
What?! Ah...!

3
00:02:23.310 --> 00:02:24.870
You mooks!

4
00:02:24.870 --> 00:02:27.060
It's your fault he got away!

5
00:02:27.060 --> 00:02:29.530
He was our golden goose!

6
00:02:30.530 --> 00:02:37.310
Dive, Dive, Dive!

7
00:02:31.870 --> 00:02:35.110
Vacate the premises!
Don't think we won't arrest all of you!

8
00:02:35.110 --> 00:02:38.680
What are you doing, Marines?!
Don't interrupt Soul King!

9
00:02:38.680 --> 00:02:41.110
Hey, what's going on in there?

10
00:02:41.110 --> 00:02:42.850
It's a riot!

11
00:02:42.850 --> 00:02:46.720
The Marines suddenly stormed in here
ready to arrest Soul King,

12
00:02:47.280 --> 00:02:50.390
but he got away because
his fans blocked his pursuers!

13
00:02:50.390 --> 00:02:53.760
Damn it all! That backstabbing...!

14
00:02:54.360 --> 00:02:56.390
That's right! This is big news!

15
00:02:56.390 --> 00:02:59.260
The musician Brook is on
Straw Hat Luffy's crew!

16
00:02:59.260 --> 00:03:00.760
He's actually a pirate!

17
00:03:07.670 --> 00:03:11.740
You have my thanks!
That's what I call good timing.

18
00:03:11.740 --> 00:03:16.580
Big Sis Shakky sent me! Your friends
should be waiting at Grove 42!

19
00:03:16.580 --> 00:03:20.080
It's been a while! My heart
is filled with anticipation!

20
00:03:20.080 --> 00:03:23.220
Oh, I don't have a heart to be filled.

21
00:03:27.220 --> 00:03:33.760
Grove 41

22
00:03:29.560 --> 00:03:30.690
That's right!

23
00:03:30.690 --> 00:03:33.630
The Marines are on the move,
and Luffy is in the area!

24
00:03:33.630 --> 00:03:38.100
We're taking the Sunny to Grove 42,
so we'll see you there!

25
00:03:38.100 --> 00:03:39.240
Roger.

26
00:03:39.940 --> 00:03:40.740
What was that?

27
00:03:40.740 --> 00:03:42.470
Hey, weren't you listening?

28
00:03:42.470 --> 00:03:44.240
How should I put this...?

29
00:03:44.880 --> 00:03:50.610
Marines. Come. We. Ship. Run.

30
00:03:51.180 --> 00:03:52.150
Understand?

31
00:03:52.150 --> 00:03:55.750
I'd understand better if you said it normally!

32
00:03:56.690 --> 00:03:59.490
But full sentences are hard for muscleheads.

33
00:03:59.490 --> 00:04:00.290
What?!

34
00:04:00.960 --> 00:04:05.260
Alright. You. Later. Slashed.

35
00:04:05.260 --> 00:04:06.660
Yeah, yeah.

36
00:04:06.660 --> 00:04:08.900
By the way, do you hear that uproar?

37
00:04:08.900 --> 00:04:09.630
Huh?

38
00:04:12.170 --> 00:04:14.840
Indeed. There. Noisy.

39
00:04:23.350 --> 00:04:25.580
Shut up, all of you!

40
00:04:28.190 --> 00:04:31.360
We've gone and found
one of the perpetrators...

41
00:04:31.360 --> 00:04:33.890
who dared to show me disrespect!

42
00:04:35.060 --> 00:04:37.090
This guy!

43
00:04:36.390 --> 00:04:37.090
Huh?

44
00:04:37.090 --> 00:04:40.230
I'll start by teaching this guy a lesson!

45
00:04:40.230 --> 00:04:44.230
He'll learn not to mess with me!

46
00:04:44.230 --> 00:04:47.370
And what I'm about to do to him...

47
00:04:47.370 --> 00:04:50.810
will be a warning to each
and every one of you!

48
00:04:50.810 --> 00:04:54.010
If you mess with me, this is
how you're gonna end up!

49
00:04:54.650 --> 00:04:56.780
You get my drift, you louts?!

50
00:04:58.220 --> 00:05:01.950
A guy with a 400-million-belly
bounty sure is scary!

51
00:05:01.950 --> 00:05:03.850
What's the matter with this guy?

52
00:05:03.850 --> 00:05:06.560
Zoro, Sanji, do you know him?

53
00:05:06.560 --> 00:05:07.120
Huh?

54
00:05:07.120 --> 00:05:08.360
You see, earlier...

55
00:05:09.860 --> 00:05:12.400
End of the line, pirates!

56
00:05:13.100 --> 00:05:17.630
Straw Hat Luffy and all his
followers will surrender now!

57
00:05:17.630 --> 00:05:18.870
Th-The Marines...?!

58
00:05:18.870 --> 00:05:23.070
We've blocked off every exit from Grove 46!

59
00:05:23.070 --> 00:05:24.980
There's no escape now!

60
00:05:25.580 --> 00:05:28.380
H... How did the Marines find out about me?

61
00:05:29.610 --> 00:05:30.950
What do you mean by that?!

62
00:05:30.950 --> 00:05:33.550
Hey, Captain! We're under siege!

63
00:05:33.550 --> 00:05:35.720
Don't panic, idiot!

64
00:05:35.720 --> 00:05:37.960
Why else would we get
all these new members?!

65
00:05:37.960 --> 00:05:40.120
Some of 'em are worth over 100 million!

66
00:05:40.120 --> 00:05:41.490
But we're outnumbered...

67
00:05:41.490 --> 00:05:42.690
Just watch, dumbass!

68
00:05:44.360 --> 00:05:46.060
Hey, Caribou!

69
00:05:46.060 --> 00:05:48.870
Use that Marine as a shield to clear a path!

70
00:05:49.470 --> 00:05:50.630
Did he say "Marine"...?

71
00:05:50.630 --> 00:05:54.270
Looks like they caught one of our scouts!

72
00:05:54.270 --> 00:05:55.440
Damn, that's not good!

73
00:05:55.910 --> 00:05:57.670
What are you doing, Caribou?!

74
00:05:57.670 --> 00:06:00.510
Using him is our ticket outta here!

75
00:06:02.080 --> 00:06:06.620
I can't do that, Big Boss!

76
00:06:05.820 --> 00:06:06.620
What?

77
00:06:07.120 --> 00:06:09.620
Because this soldier told a lie...

78
00:06:09.620 --> 00:06:13.260
He said he hadn't called the Marines yet!

79
00:06:14.860 --> 00:06:15.760
Don't do it!

80
00:06:24.840 --> 00:06:28.440
That crazy bastard ignored my order!

81
00:06:29.270 --> 00:06:31.340
Uh-oh, he did it...

82
00:06:32.110 --> 00:06:37.650
They seem to follow an underhanded rule
that lets them lie to their enemies!

83
00:06:37.650 --> 00:06:39.680
Boy, do I find that distasteful!

84
00:06:41.080 --> 00:06:44.350
So none of you have
any intention to surrender!

85
00:06:44.890 --> 00:06:46.890
After them! Get those pirates!

86
00:06:48.760 --> 00:06:53.500
Dumbasses! Our boss is worth 400 million!
He's Straw Hat Luffy, y'know?!

87
00:06:53.500 --> 00:06:55.200
Bring it on!

88
00:06:58.900 --> 00:07:00.770
This ain't good, Captain. Let's run!

89
00:07:00.770 --> 00:07:03.010
You ingrates! Listen to your captain!

90
00:07:03.010 --> 00:07:06.840
Huh? Why would they be calling me "boss"?

91
00:07:06.840 --> 00:07:09.610
Again, what do you mean by that?

92
00:07:21.060 --> 00:07:23.730
Don't them frighten you! C'mon!

93
00:07:24.960 --> 00:07:26.030
You're...

94
00:07:26.760 --> 00:07:30.830
the one worth 88 million,
Lip "Service" Doughty!

95
00:07:32.300 --> 00:07:34.740
I just love the way you fight.

96
00:07:34.740 --> 00:07:36.940
Don't be scared! Get ready to shoot!

97
00:07:41.210 --> 00:07:44.350
He's got a bounty of 92 million...

98
00:07:45.280 --> 00:07:46.980
Albion "the Maimed"!

99
00:07:49.320 --> 00:07:52.420
Don't back down! Fight for justice!

100
00:07:52.420 --> 00:07:53.420
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

101
00:07:54.830 --> 00:08:00.000
The blood of hypocrites is so smelly!

102
00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:03.470
A bounty of 210 million...
The pirate "Wet-Haired" Caribou!

103
00:08:03.870 --> 00:08:05.270
Surrender now!

104
00:08:07.070 --> 00:08:09.370
Wait... you've eaten a devil fruit?!

105
00:08:11.540 --> 00:08:13.810
You shouldn't have done that!

106
00:08:13.810 --> 00:08:16.180
It's not healthy to push yourself too hard!

107
00:08:18.320 --> 00:08:19.280
My sword...!

108
00:08:23.020 --> 00:08:25.020
Wh-Whoa! Now what's going on?!

109
00:08:25.020 --> 00:08:26.720
Pacifista!

110
00:08:26.720 --> 00:08:27.420
What?!

111
00:08:34.160 --> 00:08:36.930
Why are the Marines' human weapons here?!

112
00:08:38.470 --> 00:08:41.140
It's those guys who look like Kuma!

113
00:08:41.140 --> 00:08:43.610
But Hancock told me not to cause trouble...

114
00:08:43.610 --> 00:08:47.910
Seriously, what the hell
do you mean by that?!

115
00:08:53.320 --> 00:08:56.690
Pirate Straw Hat Luffy: Confirmed.

116
00:08:56.690 --> 00:09:00.720
Are those actual pacifista?
And they're shooting at me?!

117
00:09:02.260 --> 00:09:04.730
Pacifista, you say? How thrilling!

118
00:09:10.670 --> 00:09:16.210
88-million-belly bounty,
Lip "Service" Doughty: Subdued.

119
00:09:16.210 --> 00:09:18.080
Captain Doughty!

120
00:09:20.840 --> 00:09:24.180
Follow the pacifista! Catch the pirates!

121
00:09:24.180 --> 00:09:25.020
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

122
00:09:25.020 --> 00:09:26.620
With one shot...?!

123
00:09:26.620 --> 00:09:29.520
Even with a bounty of 88 million,
he was no match.

124
00:09:29.520 --> 00:09:32.690
This isn't goo– Wha...?!
Captain, where are you going?!

125
00:09:32.690 --> 00:09:34.420
Wait for me!

126
00:09:33.760 --> 00:09:34.420
Hey, hey!

127
00:09:34.420 --> 00:09:38.460
Morons! He wrecked Doughty,
so we've got no chance! We'd better run!

128
00:09:44.430 --> 00:09:47.170
Boss Straw Hat, do something!

129
00:09:48.140 --> 00:09:52.310
At this rate, those human weapons
are gonna wipe us all out!

130
00:09:52.310 --> 00:09:54.480
Big Boss...!

131
00:09:54.480 --> 00:09:55.350
Huh?

132
00:09:55.350 --> 00:09:57.450
Big Boss is gone!

133
00:09:57.450 --> 00:09:59.280
Big Boss?

134
00:10:00.080 --> 00:10:01.750
Do they mean Straw Hat?

135
00:10:02.450 --> 00:10:04.720
Wait! My side hurts!

136
00:10:04.720 --> 00:10:07.360
You morons...! Run, or they'll kill–

137
00:10:08.830 --> 00:10:10.560
You're in the way, idiot!

138
00:10:10.960 --> 00:10:13.130
Huh? Who are you?

139
00:10:16.700 --> 00:10:17.970
That's...

140
00:10:18.970 --> 00:10:20.040
Big Boss!

141
00:10:24.640 --> 00:10:27.440
Why are you going around as Straw Hat?

142
00:10:27.440 --> 00:10:31.780
H-H-Hey, you bastard!
Do you know who I am?!

143
00:10:31.780 --> 00:10:35.690
Move it, or I'll rip out
your guts till you're dead!

144
00:10:35.690 --> 00:10:40.860
This may come as a surprise, but I'm
the son of Dragon the Revolutionary!

145
00:10:40.860 --> 00:10:43.590
And Garp the Hero's grandson!

146
00:10:43.590 --> 00:10:48.600
I'm a big-time pirate with
a 400-million-belly bounty, Straw–

147
00:10:51.540 --> 00:10:55.170
A scumbag like you can't be Straw Hat!

148
00:10:57.940 --> 00:10:58.710
Wha...?

149
00:10:58.710 --> 00:10:59.680
Huh?

150
00:10:59.680 --> 00:11:00.880
Ah...!

151
00:11:00.880 --> 00:11:02.850
– What?!
– What?!

152
00:11:03.810 --> 00:11:07.050
Boss Straw Hat...!

153
00:11:08.080 --> 00:11:09.550
I see now.

154
00:11:09.550 --> 00:11:13.920
They all got tricked into joining
a fake Straw Hat crew.

155
00:11:13.920 --> 00:11:16.260
PX-5, who is this guy really?

156
00:11:20.400 --> 00:11:23.630
Pirate "Triple-Tongued" Demaro Black.

157
00:11:23.630 --> 00:11:26.140
Bounty: 26 million belly.

158
00:11:26.140 --> 00:11:27.000
– What?!
– What?!

159
00:11:27.000 --> 00:11:29.470
Twenty-six million? That means he's...

160
00:11:30.570 --> 00:11:32.580
– ...a fake?!
– ...a fake?!

161
00:11:34.410 --> 00:11:36.110
They found out! Run for it!

162
00:11:37.310 --> 00:11:39.280
Is this guy for real?!

163
00:11:39.280 --> 00:11:43.450
So he posed as Straw Hat
Luffy and tricked us!

164
00:11:43.450 --> 00:11:45.620
Because the real one is dead!

165
00:11:45.620 --> 00:11:51.360
Damn! I was nearly had by a weakling
with a measly 26-million-belly bounty!

166
00:11:51.360 --> 00:11:52.130
What?

167
00:11:52.930 --> 00:11:55.770
That guy was pretending to be me?

168
00:11:55.770 --> 00:11:57.370
Then, Sanji and Zoro too?

169
00:11:57.370 --> 00:12:00.140
They looked just like the real ones!

170
00:12:00.640 --> 00:12:03.540
I'd better leave before anything else happens.

171
00:12:04.110 --> 00:12:09.050
That faker is an idiot,
but you morons are also out of luck.

172
00:12:09.050 --> 00:12:11.680
You're all under arrest!

173
00:12:13.950 --> 00:12:18.560
And it just so happens that
the real Straw Hat is here too.

174
00:12:19.520 --> 00:12:23.960
PX-5 detected him when we entered this area.

175
00:12:23.960 --> 00:12:26.430
Blast him, PX-5!

176
00:12:37.240 --> 00:12:38.340
That was close!

177
00:12:41.210 --> 00:12:42.410
What are you doing?!

178
00:12:42.410 --> 00:12:45.350
This bag is holding all my precious lunches!

179
00:12:47.850 --> 00:12:50.990
His... His face...

180
00:12:55.060 --> 00:12:58.130
– It's just like the poster!
– It's just like the poster!

181
00:13:00.830 --> 00:13:03.970
That guy is the real Straw Hat!

182
00:13:03.970 --> 00:13:05.440
Stand firm!

183
00:13:05.440 --> 00:13:08.270
We came here to catch the real one anyway!

184
00:13:08.270 --> 00:13:09.010
– Aye aye!
– Aye aye!

185
00:13:09.010 --> 00:13:10.210
Straw Hat!

186
00:13:10.210 --> 00:13:13.680
What?! Are you gonna
try and stop me again?!

187
00:13:14.240 --> 00:13:17.710
I'm supposed to stay out
of trouble so I can set sail!

188
00:13:17.710 --> 00:13:20.920
Don't worry! You won't need to set sail!

189
00:13:21.350 --> 00:13:25.820
Unlike two years ago, I'm officially
a member of the Marines now!

190
00:13:25.820 --> 00:13:28.060
So, this is where I capture you!

191
00:13:28.490 --> 00:13:29.790
PX-5!

192
00:13:37.530 --> 00:13:38.700
Pretty slow...

193
00:13:42.870 --> 00:13:43.870
What?!

194
00:13:48.910 --> 00:13:50.810
Gear Second!

195
00:13:57.050 --> 00:13:58.420
Gum-Gum...

196
00:14:08.530 --> 00:14:10.400
Jet Pistol!

197
00:14:17.410 --> 00:14:18.880
Straw Hat...

198
00:14:20.040 --> 00:14:22.110
He's using haki!

199
00:14:24.950 --> 00:14:28.420
– He beat the pacifista with a single blow!
– He beat the pacifista with a single blow!

200
00:14:36.590 --> 00:14:37.830
See ya!

201
00:14:37.830 --> 00:14:40.700
I bet we'll meet again somewhere!

202
00:14:40.700 --> 00:14:42.100
Wait, Straw Hat!

203
00:14:42.100 --> 00:14:44.300
Don't let Straw Hat get away!

204
00:14:44.300 --> 00:14:45.540
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

205
00:14:47.640 --> 00:14:49.670
Hey, Luffy!

206
00:14:49.670 --> 00:14:50.570
Oh?

207
00:14:50.570 --> 00:14:53.010
Luffy! I knew it was you!

208
00:14:53.010 --> 00:14:56.010
Why are you always in trouble?!

209
00:14:56.510 --> 00:14:58.380
Ohhh!

210
00:14:58.380 --> 00:15:03.220
No mistake this time! It's been a while, guys!

211
00:15:03.220 --> 00:15:06.990
Roronoa! Black Leg! So they're alive too?!

212
00:15:06.990 --> 00:15:08.790
PX-7!

213
00:15:16.930 --> 00:15:18.900
– Outta my way!
– Outta my way!

214
00:15:24.340 --> 00:15:25.640
I cut him!

215
00:15:25.640 --> 00:15:28.010
No, I broke his neck!

216
00:15:30.110 --> 00:15:33.280
It's the Straw Hats! The real ones!

217
00:15:33.280 --> 00:15:36.390
They're nothing like the fake Straw Hats!

218
00:15:41.560 --> 00:15:43.730
Hey, Luffy, you're the ninth.

219
00:15:43.730 --> 00:15:45.900
Shut up! Imagine gloating about that!

220
00:15:45.900 --> 00:15:48.330
C'mon, Luffy! Everyone's on the ship!

221
00:15:48.330 --> 00:15:49.170
Okay!

222
00:15:50.900 --> 00:15:54.440
Don't let them get away!
Catch them at any cost!

223
00:15:54.440 --> 00:15:55.240
– Aye aye!
– Aye aye!

224
00:15:55.240 --> 00:16:00.180
It's been a really long time!
I wonder how everybody is!

225
00:16:00.180 --> 00:16:01.850
I'm so happy!

226
00:16:09.390 --> 00:16:10.850
Hey, what's wrong?

227
00:16:13.890 --> 00:16:14.690
Oh!

228
00:16:16.030 --> 00:16:19.000
Rayleigh!

229
00:16:19.000 --> 00:16:20.560
What?!

230
00:16:20.560 --> 00:16:22.230
No way!

231
00:16:23.170 --> 00:16:24.970
Dark King Rayleigh?!

232
00:16:28.710 --> 00:16:32.710
I wanted to check on you,
but you seem to be doing just fine.

233
00:16:33.380 --> 00:16:36.250
You've refined your skills even further.

234
00:16:36.250 --> 00:16:37.310
Uh-huh!

235
00:16:37.710 --> 00:16:41.220
Now get going! Your friends are waiting.

236
00:16:41.220 --> 00:16:46.890
Uh-huh! Rayleigh, thank you
for everything these past two years!

237
00:16:48.060 --> 00:16:51.260
This isn't like you at all. Just go!

238
00:17:00.700 --> 00:17:01.470
Rayleigh!

239
00:17:04.170 --> 00:17:05.640
I'll do it!

240
00:17:09.480 --> 00:17:15.320
I'm gonna become King of the Pirates!

241
00:17:28.360 --> 00:17:29.730
What are you guys doing?!

242
00:17:29.730 --> 00:17:31.570
Get Straw Hat already!

243
00:17:32.500 --> 00:17:33.540
Oops!

244
00:17:33.540 --> 00:17:35.270
Hurry up, Luffy!

245
00:17:35.270 --> 00:17:37.170
Rayleigh, thank you for everything!

246
00:17:37.170 --> 00:17:39.140
Well then, Rayleigh...!

247
00:17:40.040 --> 00:17:42.410
Thanks again for everything!

248
00:17:42.410 --> 00:17:45.180
I'm going now!

249
00:17:49.720 --> 00:17:50.750
Yes...

250
00:18:08.540 --> 00:18:09.970
They went that way!

251
00:18:09.970 --> 00:18:11.910
– After them!
– Don't let them escape!

252
00:18:14.510 --> 00:18:16.750
Rise to the top!

253
00:18:19.650 --> 00:18:23.790
The Straw Hats are heading for Grove 42!

254
00:18:23.790 --> 00:18:25.860
Don't let them get away!

255
00:18:30.330 --> 00:18:31.790
What was that?

256
00:18:34.000 --> 00:18:36.170
Dark King Rayleigh!

257
00:18:36.170 --> 00:18:38.500
It's a new beginning for my pupil!

258
00:18:38.500 --> 00:18:40.370
Don't be too hard on him.

259
00:18:43.240 --> 00:18:45.480
Wh-What is this line?

260
00:18:46.380 --> 00:18:49.310
I do not recommend crossing it.

261
00:18:54.680 --> 00:18:58.120
Oh, bubble bags! There're so many!

262
00:18:58.120 --> 00:18:59.520
What's in them?

263
00:18:59.520 --> 00:19:05.760
They're filled with food. I imagine everyone's
stomachs got bigger over the past two years.

264
00:19:05.760 --> 00:19:07.900
I'll let you fill up later!

265
00:19:07.900 --> 00:19:11.130
Really?! I can't wait to eat your cooking!

266
00:19:11.130 --> 00:19:13.470
There they are! They're this way!

267
00:19:14.970 --> 00:19:16.910
Oh? They circled ahead!

268
00:19:18.170 --> 00:19:19.710
No choice, huh?

269
00:19:19.710 --> 00:19:21.710
Everybody, charge!

270
00:19:21.710 --> 00:19:22.850
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

271
00:19:27.150 --> 00:19:29.690
I wanna... become a flea...

272
00:19:29.690 --> 00:19:31.220
What's wrong? What're you...?

273
00:19:31.220 --> 00:19:33.220
I wanna become a mite...

274
00:19:33.220 --> 00:19:34.690
What?!

275
00:19:34.690 --> 00:19:36.460
What in the world...?

276
00:19:40.660 --> 00:19:42.270
I... I...

277
00:19:43.230 --> 00:19:45.840
I wanna become a louse...

278
00:19:45.840 --> 00:19:47.140
Hey!

279
00:19:47.140 --> 00:19:48.400
It must be...

280
00:19:51.670 --> 00:19:53.640
As I suspected,

281
00:19:53.640 --> 00:19:55.480
this mess is your doing.

282
00:19:57.250 --> 00:19:58.850
I can't believe it!

283
00:20:00.150 --> 00:20:03.520
You haven't gotten anywhere yet!

284
00:20:03.520 --> 00:20:06.920
That's right! I remember you from Thriller Bark!

285
00:20:07.590 --> 00:20:08.830
She was...?

286
00:20:08.830 --> 00:20:11.990
What are you still doing here?

287
00:20:11.990 --> 00:20:15.930
You should be nicer to the one
who brought you back to this island!

288
00:20:15.930 --> 00:20:18.170
If I hadn't directed you, why, you'd be...

289
00:20:19.900 --> 00:20:22.410
Just try a little gratitu–

290
00:20:23.810 --> 00:20:26.540
A real woman! A real woman!

291
00:20:26.540 --> 00:20:29.010
Of course I am! What,
are you sick in the head?

292
00:20:29.010 --> 00:20:31.580
Anyway, set sail already!

293
00:20:31.580 --> 00:20:33.680
I saw some Marine ships around here!

294
00:20:33.680 --> 00:20:34.550
– What?
– What?

295
00:20:35.180 --> 00:20:37.590
Soon, there'll be no way out!

296
00:20:37.690 --> 00:20:42.460
The Straw Hats' Rendezvous Point, Grove 42 Shore

297
00:20:42.460 --> 00:20:43.530
Oh?!

298
00:20:43.530 --> 00:20:44.690
That voice...!

299
00:20:44.690 --> 00:20:49.430
Usopp! Nami! Robin!

300
00:20:49.430 --> 00:20:52.670
♪ Frrranky! ♪

301
00:20:57.110 --> 00:20:57.910
Brook!

302
00:20:57.910 --> 00:21:00.910
Hey! I can't believe you abandoned stardom!

303
00:21:00.910 --> 00:21:01.640
Attaboy!

304
00:21:04.150 --> 00:21:07.020
It's been a long time, everybody!

305
00:21:07.020 --> 00:21:10.720
You two have become even more beautiful!

306
00:21:13.590 --> 00:21:14.920
Alright, Nami...

307
00:21:15.360 --> 00:21:16.860
it's been two years, so...

308
00:21:18.830 --> 00:21:21.600
Oh, are you gonna sing for us?

309
00:21:25.540 --> 00:21:28.000
...would you be so kind
as to show me your pa–

310
00:21:28.000 --> 00:21:29.810
What do you think?!

311
00:21:29.810 --> 00:21:32.880
I never let you see them two years ago either!

312
00:21:32.880 --> 00:21:36.210
I-I'm so excited to see you again... See?

313
00:21:36.210 --> 00:21:39.980
It's... making my heart quiver. Although...

314
00:21:39.980 --> 00:21:44.250
I don't have a heart that can quiver...

315
00:21:40.720 --> 00:21:44.250
Hey...! The rock star is having convulsions.

316
00:21:44.250 --> 00:21:48.320
Honestly! None of you guys have grown up.

317
00:21:49.490 --> 00:21:50.730
By the way...

318
00:21:51.430 --> 00:21:54.700
Looks like we're missing a few members.

319
00:21:54.700 --> 00:21:58.170
Oh, right. Chopper went to pick them up–

320
00:21:56.870 --> 00:21:58.630
Hey!

321
00:21:58.170 --> 00:21:58.630
– Huh?
– Huh?

322
00:22:05.810 --> 00:22:07.480
They're finally here!

323
00:22:07.480 --> 00:22:10.080
Wow, hey!

324
00:22:11.980 --> 00:22:14.480
Everybody!

325
00:22:16.590 --> 00:22:18.920
I found them!

326
00:22:20.420 --> 00:22:23.430
Luffy! Zoro! Sanji!

327
00:22:23.430 --> 00:22:25.660
Hey!

328
00:22:27.630 --> 00:22:31.430
Luffy! I missed you so much!

329
00:22:31.430 --> 00:22:34.500
You guys sure do look manlier!

330
00:22:36.740 --> 00:22:38.670
We're all back together again!

331
00:22:42.510 --> 00:22:43.350
Finally–

332
00:22:43.350 --> 00:22:44.210
Oh!

333
00:22:44.210 --> 00:22:46.620
Guys!

334
00:22:55.120 --> 00:22:57.290
What?!

335
00:22:58.060 --> 00:23:00.230
Sanji!

336
00:23:06.570 --> 00:23:08.540
Well then, thank you!

337
00:23:08.540 --> 00:23:10.870
Tell everyone in the Birdie Kingdom I said hi!

338
00:23:12.610 --> 00:23:14.810
Usopp! Is Sanji alright?!

339
00:23:14.810 --> 00:23:18.010
One... One... One beautiful woman...

340
00:23:18.010 --> 00:23:20.520
Hey, stay with me!

341
00:23:18.910 --> 00:23:20.520
Two beautiful women...

342
00:23:20.520 --> 00:23:23.320
Chopper, this is real bad!
We've gotta stop the bleeding!

343
00:23:25.020 --> 00:23:27.960
F-F-Franky, you're...!

344
00:23:27.960 --> 00:23:29.490
What's the matter?

345
00:23:30.590 --> 00:23:33.760
Is there something that concerns you-mecha?

346
00:23:34.300 --> 00:23:37.200
"Mecha"?! I wanna try too!

347
00:23:36.230 --> 00:23:37.200
Wait, Luffy!

348
00:23:37.970 --> 00:23:39.640
Leave that crap for later!

349
00:23:39.640 --> 00:23:42.970
It looks like the Marine ships are already here!

350
00:23:45.880 --> 00:23:48.010
Oh, no! When did they get here?!

351
00:23:50.280 --> 00:23:52.420
Three Marine ships!

352
00:23:55.580 --> 00:23:58.290
Hey, should we fight?!
They're gaining on us!

353
00:23:58.290 --> 00:24:01.220
Fire! Send them to the depths!

354
00:24:04.730 --> 00:24:05.660
Slave...

355
00:24:06.460 --> 00:24:07.130
Arrow!

356
00:24:13.500 --> 00:24:15.440
Wha...? What just happened?

357
00:24:15.440 --> 00:24:17.270
I-It's...

358
00:24:20.540 --> 00:24:22.580
The Kuja Pirates!

359
00:24:24.910 --> 00:24:26.220
Who...

360
00:24:27.920 --> 00:24:30.390
put a Marine ship...

361
00:24:31.950 --> 00:24:34.090
in my way?

362
00:24:42.400 --> 00:24:44.370
That's the Kuja emblem!

363
00:24:44.370 --> 00:24:45.870
The "Kuja"?

364
00:24:45.870 --> 00:24:50.710
They're strong Amazonian pirates led
by the Pirate Empress, one of the Warlords.

365
00:24:50.710 --> 00:24:52.110
A Warlord?!

366
00:24:52.110 --> 00:24:54.180
Empress Boa Hancock.

367
00:24:54.180 --> 00:25:00.250
They say anyone who sees her
becomes infatuated and turns to stone.

368
00:25:00.250 --> 00:25:03.320
Oh, too bright! She is dazzling!

369
00:25:03.320 --> 00:25:05.690
There is no end to her beauty!

370
00:25:05.690 --> 00:25:08.390
You weren't kidding! She's a goddess!

371
00:25:09.260 --> 00:25:10.860
Goddess?!

372
00:25:10.860 --> 00:25:11.830
Where is she?!

373
00:25:11.830 --> 00:25:13.600
Goddess? Goddess?

374
00:25:14.160 --> 00:25:18.030
Goddess... Oh, goddess... Oh, goddess... G... G... Goddess...

375
00:25:18.770 --> 00:25:20.370
He turned to stone!

376
00:25:21.170 --> 00:25:23.010
Hey, that's Hancock and her pirates!

377
00:25:23.010 --> 00:25:23.710
– Huh?
– Huh?

378
00:25:24.570 --> 00:25:27.310
Move your ship, Boa Hancock!

379
00:25:27.310 --> 00:25:29.710
Don't interfere with our duty!

380
00:25:29.710 --> 00:25:34.980
Cease your baseless accusations! I just
can't be bothered to move out of the way.

381
00:25:34.980 --> 00:25:37.190
Sh-She's acting like a child!

382
00:25:37.650 --> 00:25:38.790
Is that a problem?

383
00:25:40.890 --> 00:25:44.060
Go, Luffy... I made an opening for you!

384
00:25:44.860 --> 00:25:48.700
She just winked at us...

385
00:25:48.700 --> 00:25:51.070
She helped us. Let's set sail now!

386
00:25:51.070 --> 00:25:52.940
You know that Warlord?

387
00:25:52.940 --> 00:25:57.640
Yeah... I was sent to the Isle of Women
and became friends with them.

388
00:25:57.640 --> 00:26:00.810
Isn't that the legendary island of women?

389
00:26:00.810 --> 00:26:02.080
It really exists?

390
00:26:02.680 --> 00:26:05.510
You're friends with the Pirate Empress?!

391
00:26:05.510 --> 00:26:09.890
Hey! Did you even get any training done?!

392
00:26:09.890 --> 00:26:11.050
Yeah, I'm all set!

393
00:26:11.050 --> 00:26:14.890
Damn... It's not fair...! It's not fair...!

394
00:26:14.890 --> 00:26:16.460
What's the matter, Sanji?

395
00:26:17.360 --> 00:26:20.400
Whoa, so they're Luffy's friends!

396
00:26:20.400 --> 00:26:23.830
There are a bunch of creatures
that I've never seen before.

397
00:26:23.830 --> 00:26:26.470
– One, two, three, four...
– Looks like they're having fun!

398
00:26:27.170 --> 00:26:30.140
Okay, let's get ready to set sail now!

399
00:26:30.140 --> 00:26:31.910
– Yeah!
– Yes, Nami my sweet!

400
00:26:31.910 --> 00:26:34.940
Huh? What's the matter, Usopp?

401
00:26:34.940 --> 00:26:39.050
It's just that... Did you guys
beat back all those Marines?

402
00:26:39.050 --> 00:26:43.720
No. We could still hear them
shouting as we were flying away.

403
00:26:44.620 --> 00:26:47.820
Then, why aren't they coming
after us from inland?

404
00:26:55.430 --> 00:26:57.670
This is Reinforcement Platoon 3!

405
00:26:57.670 --> 00:26:58.770
Can you hear me?

406
00:27:00.000 --> 00:27:01.970
What's wrong? What happened?

407
00:27:01.970 --> 00:27:04.610
We can't get to Grove 42!

408
00:27:04.610 --> 00:27:05.710
Why not?!

409
00:27:05.710 --> 00:27:07.740
B-Because...

410
00:27:07.740 --> 00:27:10.550
there are huge bugs standing in our way!

411
00:27:10.550 --> 00:27:12.010
What? Bugs?!

412
00:27:14.920 --> 00:27:16.650
What are they?!

413
00:27:20.420 --> 00:27:21.760
Fire!

414
00:27:29.200 --> 00:27:33.270
I won't let them mess
with Usopp'n's new adventure'n!

415
00:27:36.670 --> 00:27:39.440
When men part ways, we don't shed tears'n.

416
00:27:40.540 --> 00:27:43.650
Good luck, Usopp'n!

417
00:27:45.110 --> 00:27:47.550
As long as they're not coming, that's good.

418
00:27:47.550 --> 00:27:50.050
Their trouble is our luck.

419
00:27:50.050 --> 00:27:52.350
Let's just leave now!

420
00:27:52.350 --> 00:27:54.720
Nami, lead the way!

421
00:27:54.720 --> 00:27:55.520
Leave it to me!

422
00:27:57.560 --> 00:27:58.330
Alright!

423
00:28:00.830 --> 00:28:02.030
This is Platoon 4.

424
00:28:02.030 --> 00:28:03.770
I'm sorry.

425
00:28:03.770 --> 00:28:07.100
We got caught in a sudden downpour, and now the gunpowder is wet!

426
00:28:07.100 --> 00:28:08.800
Rain? Where is it raining?

427
00:28:08.800 --> 00:28:10.140
Rain? Where is it raining?

428
00:28:10.140 --> 00:28:14.210
Sabaody Archipelago should be
clear and sunny today!

429
00:28:17.950 --> 00:28:19.780
No thunder.

430
00:28:19.780 --> 00:28:23.050
We want to avoid hurting civilians.

431
00:28:23.050 --> 00:28:26.060
The bubbles here are a pain in the neck...

432
00:28:26.060 --> 00:28:29.660
But it's hard to believe
we caught such perfect wind.

433
00:28:29.660 --> 00:28:32.600
It brought us right to Sabaody Archipelago.

434
00:28:32.600 --> 00:28:36.570
That's because Nami's a natural at this.

435
00:28:40.100 --> 00:28:45.670
Best of luck! We'll miss you
up here on Weatheria!

436
00:29:02.420 --> 00:29:03.730
Oh, it's inflating!

437
00:29:05.660 --> 00:29:08.530
What? This jelly inflates?

438
00:29:12.070 --> 00:29:15.070
Oh, we got a bubble roof!

439
00:29:15.740 --> 00:29:16.710
Listen, everyone.

440
00:29:17.440 --> 00:29:22.180
A coated ship can mitigate
any kind of pressure.

441
00:29:22.180 --> 00:29:27.680
Once Franky removes the buoyancy bag
supporting the ship's keel,

442
00:29:27.680 --> 00:29:31.620
the Sunny's coating will make her start to sink.

443
00:29:31.620 --> 00:29:32.620
That's how it works.

444
00:29:32.620 --> 00:29:34.220
– I see.
– I see.

445
00:29:34.220 --> 00:29:35.690
Too complicated, huh?

446
00:29:35.690 --> 00:29:37.830
Anyway, lower the sail now!

447
00:29:37.830 --> 00:29:38.660
– The sail?
– The sail?

448
00:29:38.660 --> 00:29:42.830
Rather than the wind, sea currents
drive a coated sailing ship.

449
00:29:42.830 --> 00:29:45.870
So it doesn't just sink to where it's going.

450
00:29:46.540 --> 00:29:49.370
Alright! Let's hurry before we
run into more Marines!

451
00:29:50.710 --> 00:29:54.080
This is Central Platoon 5 at Grove 42!

452
00:29:54.080 --> 00:29:55.740
We have an emergency!

453
00:29:55.740 --> 00:29:59.650
The troops that came before us,
Platoon 2, seem to have become negative!

454
00:29:59.650 --> 00:30:01.780
What are you talking about? "Negative"?!

455
00:30:01.780 --> 00:30:03.050
I wanna become like moss...

456
00:30:03.050 --> 00:30:05.850
I'm no good. I wanna become a water flea...

457
00:30:05.850 --> 00:30:10.630
According to them, Straw Hat Luffy
got on a giant bird and flew away!

458
00:30:10.630 --> 00:30:13.200
Bird? What are you guys doing now?!

459
00:30:13.200 --> 00:30:16.030
We're fighting against unknown enemies!

460
00:30:17.200 --> 00:30:20.870
Marine reinforcements!
We were about to leave...

461
00:30:20.870 --> 00:30:22.740
Everybody!

462
00:30:24.740 --> 00:30:27.340
Straw Hat's ship is in range now!

463
00:30:28.510 --> 00:30:31.510
Wait a minute! A giant bird
is coming toward us!

464
00:30:41.490 --> 00:30:42.990
It's him!

465
00:30:44.530 --> 00:30:45.860
They're behind us!

466
00:30:45.860 --> 00:30:47.160
I got it!

467
00:30:49.770 --> 00:30:51.100
How's that, Nami?

468
00:30:51.100 --> 00:30:53.300
Please watch me...

469
00:30:53.300 --> 00:30:55.800
See how much stronger I've become.

470
00:30:55.800 --> 00:30:58.070
Sanji!

471
00:31:00.540 --> 00:31:03.550
Respond, Platoon 5! What's going on?!

472
00:31:03.550 --> 00:31:05.610
W-We're...

473
00:31:05.610 --> 00:31:10.250
We're facing... an unexpected obstacle...

474
00:31:10.250 --> 00:31:11.750
Don't do it!

475
00:31:14.220 --> 00:31:18.260
How dare you reject us like that!

476
00:31:18.260 --> 00:31:20.700
Maybe they're all shy.

477
00:31:20.700 --> 00:31:23.600
You don't have to be ashamed!

478
00:31:24.200 --> 00:31:27.140
Let's go out for tea sometime!

479
00:31:27.900 --> 00:31:31.810
I-I-I'm going... I'm going crazy, aren't I?!

480
00:31:34.440 --> 00:31:38.210
Oh! You've got such a cute face!

481
00:31:38.210 --> 00:31:39.350
No, don't do it!

482
00:31:42.250 --> 00:31:44.920
What's wrong? Answer, Platoon 5!

483
00:31:46.760 --> 00:31:49.020
Sanji-kins, now's your chance!

484
00:31:51.460 --> 00:31:53.900
Hey, hey, what's wrong, Sanji?!

485
00:31:55.060 --> 00:32:00.240
I-I-I don't know... Suddenly, it felt like
someone was squeezing my heart...

486
00:32:00.240 --> 00:32:01.870
I removed the buoyancy bag!

487
00:32:01.870 --> 00:32:04.040
Okay! And the sail?!

488
00:32:04.040 --> 00:32:06.340
Ready when you are!

489
00:32:06.910 --> 00:32:08.410
Is it time to go, Nami?

490
00:32:08.410 --> 00:32:10.410
Yes, at your command, Captain.

491
00:32:17.750 --> 00:32:18.920
Alright...

492
00:32:23.430 --> 00:32:25.130
You guys!

493
00:32:26.260 --> 00:32:31.230
I have so much I'd like
to tell all of you, but first,

494
00:32:31.230 --> 00:32:35.240
thank you for going along with
my selfish decision for two years!

495
00:32:35.240 --> 00:32:38.040
It's not as if it was the first time.

496
00:32:38.040 --> 00:32:41.240
He's right! You've always been that way!

497
00:32:45.810 --> 00:32:49.720
Rear Admiral, the pirate ship is submerging!

498
00:32:49.720 --> 00:32:51.720
What?! Curses!

499
00:32:51.720 --> 00:32:53.090
Damn you!

500
00:32:53.090 --> 00:32:54.990
Do you have any idea...

501
00:32:54.990 --> 00:32:57.560
how heinous those pirates are? Hey!

502
00:32:57.560 --> 00:32:58.990
Rear Admiral!

503
00:32:59.960 --> 00:33:02.530
Take care, Luffy...

504
00:33:05.400 --> 00:33:07.570
Let down the sail!

505
00:33:07.570 --> 00:33:08.700
– Yes!
– Yeah!

506
00:33:16.410 --> 00:33:19.410
Set sail!

507
00:33:19.410 --> 00:33:21.780
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

508
00:33:28.290 --> 00:33:32.290
Let's go to Fishman Island!
